revision.text:
The '''3rd [[Central American and Caribbean Games]]''' were staged in [[San Salvador]] in [[El Salvador]]. They were held from 16 March to 5 April 1935, and featured 741 athletes from nine nations, competing in fourteen sports (diving and swimming counted as individual sports).

