{{Infobox music festival | name =Olympia Experimental Music Festival | image =Image:Dendrites (band) 09A.jpg | caption =Portland, Oregon band Dendrites perform at the 14th Olympia Experimental Music Festival, 2008. | location =[[Olympia, Washington]] | years_active =1995-present | founders =L. Jim McAdams | dates = | genre = [[Electronic music]], [[experimental music]] | attendance = | capacity = | website =[http://www.myspace.com/olystrangemusic Olympia Strange Music MySpace page] }} The '''Olympia Experimental Music Festival''', also known for a time as '''The Olympia Festival of Experimental Musics''',<ref name=TheStranger1>Christopher Delaurenti, [http://www.thestranger.com/seattle/Content?oid=14736 Classical, Jazz, & Avant: Experimental Music Festival], ''[[The Stranger (newspaper)|The Stranger]]'', June 26 – July 2, 2003 issue. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> has been produced annually in [[Olympia, Washington]] since 1995.<ref>Tiffany Lee Brown, [http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly.html Bleepy-Bloopy Noises: Creepy-crawly creatures emerge for the Olympia Experimental Music Festival] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071115191454/http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly.html |date=November 15, 2007 }}, ''Signum'' magazine, ''Marrow'' section, issue 12, 2001. Accessed online July 3, 2008. Refers to the 2001 festival as "the 7th Annual".</ref> Organizers have included festival founder L. Jim McAdams,<ref name=Brown2>Tiffany Lee Brown, "Bleepy-Bloopy Noises", [http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly2.html page 2] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212102444/http://incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly2.html |date=December 12, 2007 }}. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> [[Arrington de Dionyso]] (founder of the Olympia Strange Music Society),<ref name=Brown2 /> Aerick Duckhugger,<ref name=Brown2/> and Domenica Clark.<ref name=14-10>Program, 14th Olympia Experimental Music Festival, p. 10.</ref> During de Dionyso's tenure as chief organizer (festivals 9–12) the festival was primarily known by the alternate name ''The Olympia Festival of Experimental Musics''.{{Citation needed|date=July 2008}}
==History== [[Image:Crank Sturgeon 13A.jpg|thumb|left|Portland, Maine performance artist [[Crank Sturgeon]] performs at the 14th Olympia Experimental Music Festival, 2008.]]
Performers have included Acre,<ref name=Yahoo-2007>[http://upcoming.yahoo.com/event/193910/ Olympia Experimental Music Festival], 13th Annual Olympia Experimental Music Festival (2007) listing on [[Yahoo!]] Upcoming Events and Things To Do. Accessed July 7, 2008.</ref> Alps of New South Wales,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> A Nat Hema,<ref name=Brown7>Tiffany Lee Brown, "Bleepy-Bloopy Noises", [http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly7.html page 7]. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> Wendy Atkinson,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Atropy Minor,<ref name=Brown7 /> Argumentix,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Better People,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Blue Sabbath Black Cheer,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Bran Flakes,<ref name=Brown4>Tiffany Lee Brown, "Bleepy-Bloopy Noises", [http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly4.html page 4]. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> Cabinet of Natural Curiosities,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Celesteville,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> [[Crank Sturgeon]],<ref name=14-4>Program, 14th Olympia Experimental Music Festival, p. 4.</ref> [[Dead Air Fresheners]],<ref name=14-4 /><ref name=Brown3>Tiffany Lee Brown, "Bleepy-Bloopy Noises", [http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly3.html page 3] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212102401/http://incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly3.html |date=December 12, 2007 }}. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> [[Amy Denio]],<ref name=14-3>Program, 14th Olympia Experimental Music Festival, p. 3.</ref> Dendrites,<ref name=14-4 /> Arrington de Dionyso, Paul Dutton, [[Evolution Control Committee]],<ref name=Brown6>Tiffany Lee Brown, "Bleepy-Bloopy Noises", [http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly6.html page 6]. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> [[Steve Fisk]],<ref name=14-4 /><ref name=Brown6 /> Foque Mopus,<ref name=14-3 /> Gang Wizard,<ref name=Brown2 /> Hans Grusel's Krankenkabinet,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> [[Bill Horist]],<ref name=14-3 /> KnotPineBox,<ref name=14-4 /> Al Larsen, Le Ton Mite, METAL,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Midmight,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Nequaquam Vacuum,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Noggin,<ref name=TheStranger1 /> Noisettes,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Office Products, Oliver Squash,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Plants,<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> [[Gino Robair]],<ref name=TheStranger1 /> Sluggo,<ref name=Brown6 /> [[Chuck Swaim]],<ref name=Brown4 /> Jennifer Robin,<ref name=Brown1>Tiffany Lee Brown, "Bleepy-Bloopy Noises",[http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly.html page 1] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071115191454/http://www.incunabula.org/signum/Issue12/marrow/Oly/oly.html |date=November 15, 2007 }}. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> [[Adam Forkner|White Rainbow]],<ref name=Yahoo-2007 /> Bert Wilson,<ref name=TheStranger1 /> Wood Paneling,<ref name=TheStranger1 /><ref name=Yahoo-2007 /><ref name=Brown3 /> Paintings for Animals,<ref name=Ahrendt /> LA Lungs,<ref name=Ahrendt /> Four Dimensional Nightmare,<ref name=Ahrendt /> Super Unity, Eurostache,<ref name=Ahrendt>{{cite web|last=Ahrendt|first=Daniel|title=Olympia Experimental Music Festival: Paintings for Animals, LA Lungs, Eurostache, and More|url=http://www.ssgmusic.com/olympia-experimental-music-festival-paintings-for-animals-la-lungs-eurostache-and-more/|publisher=SSG Music|accessdate=June 26, 2011}}</ref> and Nathan Cearley (at the time performing as Godzilla).
In addition to unusual, experimental, and/or noise music, many festival performers use film, multimedia, and spoken word. [[Yahoo News]] in 2007 called it a "summer festival to watch".<ref>Author unknown, [http://upcoming.yahoo.com/news/archives/2007/06/18/summer_f/ Yahoo Upcoming]. Accessed online July 3, 2008.</ref> In ''Signum'', writer [[Tiffany Lee Brown]] commented in 2001: "This was no overpriced, fancypants event full of goatee-stroking theorizers or a showcase of overserious minimalist compositions, but a romp through the tangled underbrush of homegrown experimentalism."<ref name=Brown1 />
