{{Infobox recurring event | name = Tokyo Idol Festival | native_name = TOKYO IDOL FESTIVAL | logo = | logo_caption = | image = <!--DO NOT include "File:" part of image name (different from above because of merger with Template:Infobox festival)--> | imagesize = | caption = | date = <!--"dates=" also works, as merged from Template:Infobox festival. Do not use both--> | begins = | ends = | next = | frequency = Annually | location = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] | years_active = | first = August 2010 | prev = August 2017 | last = | participants = | attendance = 80,000 (2017) | genre = | budget = | patron = | organised = | website = {{URL|www.idolfes.com/}} | footnotes = }} {{nihongo|'''Tokyo Idol Festival'''|TOKYO IDOL FESTIVAL||also abbreviated as TIF}} is an annual event featuring live performances from female [[Japanese idol|solo idols and idol groups]] from all over [[Japan]]. The festival has been held since 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://natalie.mu/music/pp/niconata03|title=ナタリー - [Power Push] ニコナタ（音楽）アイドリング!!!インタビュー (1-2)|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|accessdate=2013-11-16|language=Japanese}}</ref>
In 2014, [[The Wall Street Journal]] blog estimated that TIF is one of 5 places in Japan to enjoy summer music festivals.<ref>{{cite web|title=5 Places in Japan to Enjoy Summer Music Festivals|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/briefly/2014/07/24/5-places-in-japan-to-enjoy-summer-music-festivals/}}</ref>
More than 200 idol groups, about 1500 idols performed and attracted more than 80,000 spectators in 2017.
